Let’s be real
Every Angular project has the same repetitive problems
focus issues, scroll tracking, click-outside, shortcuts, lazy images
And every junior solves them inside components.
But seniors?
They build directives once and reuse them forever.
1) clickOutside Directive (Must-Have)
Dropdown, modals, popovers .
@Directive({
selector: '[clickOutside]',
standalone: true
})
export class ClickOutsideDirective {
@Output() clickOutside = new EventEmitter<void>();@HostListener('document:click', ['$event.target'])
onClick(target: any) {
if (!this.el.nativeElement.contains(target)) {
this.clickOutside.emit();
}
}constructor(private el: ElementRef) {}
}Usage:
<div (clickOutside)="closeMenu()"></div>2) autoFocus Directive
